    {
      "id": "f0b11da66b33749c29e36db3f44e16531c4358f2",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 130,
        "name": "Nikitas Angelinas",
        "email": "nikitas.angelinas@hpe.com",
        "username": "nikitas_angelinas"
      },
      "date": "2013-03-08 22:20:55.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nIs there a way to re-submit this for testing in Maloo without refreshing the patch? I can't seem to find this.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "91f1299e499377d486540f2e447346c5feb8ec29",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-03-08 23:17:33.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nNikitas,\nyes it is possible to resubmit the patch for testing once we know the existing bug that caused the failure.  We can't resubmit the patch without associating it to a specific LU ticket for the failure.\n\nI note that both the ZFS and ldiskfs tests failed with lustre-initialization-1, which means that Lustre couldn't even be mounted.  If you could look through the test failures, in particular the \"autotest\" log to see why this failed, since it might also relate to your patch in some way (e.g. missing symbol at module load time).",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "901a7cdc404fd0e481f291527b310b4be0fba96b",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-03-14 21:59:38.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Looks good to me, approved\n\n(1 inline comment)\n\nIf the earlier NRS policy patches are refreshed, these changes should be merged into the actual policy patches so that we have fewer patches to track and we don't have to fix new code.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "c249e4d4620cfe44ab89f758010ea252aaee1b3b",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 130,
        "name": "Nikitas Angelinas",
        "email": "nikitas.angelinas@hpe.com",
        "username": "nikitas_angelinas"
      },
      "date": "2013-03-25 16:36:08.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Abandoned\n\nBased on Andreas' suggestion, I am abandoning this change, and merging the code into the NRS framework follow-up and policies patches, so that there are fewer patches to keep track of.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
